lights_district_moonwake_port.name: Lights District - Moonwake Port
lights_district_moonwake_port.description: Both air and sea come and leave from here, all expertly designed into one section to minimize space taken up. This is where your journey in Reverie City probably began!

lights_district_central_plaza.name: Lights District - Central Plaza
lights_district_central_plaza.description: The heart of the Lights District. Electronic billboards stretch across the skyscrapers lining the streets, with announcements and footage of official Pokemon battles occurring in the arena playing on the center big screen.

lights_district_art_studio.name: Lights District - Art Studio
lights_district_art_studio.description: A creative loft covered in neon graffiti, rotating murals, and augmented-reality projections. Trainers collaborate with artists while sketching ideas for their next battle strategies.

wild_area_forest_meadow_path.name: Wild Area α - Forest: Meadow Path
wild_area_forest_meadow_path.description: A peaceful meadow at the edge of the forest, filled with wildflowers and gentle Pokémon. The perfect starting point for new trainers to begin their wild area adventures.

wild_area_canyon_redstone_canyon.name: Wild Area β - Canyon: Redstone Canyon
wild_area_canyon_redstone_canyon.description: A rugged canyon carved by ancient rivers, with red stone cliffs and rocky outcrops. Rock and Ground-type Pokémon make their homes in the caves and ledges throughout the area.

wild_area_desert_sunbaked_path.name: Wild Area γ - Desert: Sandy Crossing
wild_area_desert_sunbaked_path.description: The outskirts of a vast desert, where the ground begins to turn sandy under the scorching sun. Hardy Pokémon adapted to heat and arid conditions can be found here.

wild_area_tundra_snowdust_crossing.name: Wild Area δ - Tundra: Snowdust Crossing
wild_area_tundra_snowdust_crossing.description: A frozen path through the tundra where snow falls year-round. Ice and hardy Pokémon brave the cold winds and bitter temperatures of this unforgiving landscape.

lights_district_crossings.name: Lights District - Crossings
lights_district_crossings.description: One of the various crossings in the Lights district. With all the heavy foot traffic, there's lots of little bits of food that can be found on the floor. For a little bit, anyway, before it's found by one of the various Pokemon that can be found here.

lights_district_streets.name: Lights District - Streets
lights_district_streets.description: One of the various streets in the Lights District. Electricity flows through the city. Every building, every sign, every street. Electric Pokemon are drawn to it, but only the smallest tend to be able to thrive in the busy streets alongside a few birds and rodents.

lights_district_alleyways.name: Lights District - Alleyways
lights_district_alleyways.description: While the absolute majority of the city lights up there are a few nooks and crevices that are dark. Damp and dark alleyways creating shortcuts between buildings, where trash bins can be found. A few Pokemon tend to thrive here, though.

lights_district_wild_zone_1.name: Lights District - Wild Zone 1
lights_district_wild_zone_1.description: The Lights District Gardens. A little life existing amongst the glass, concrete and metal towers, vibrant green grass with an assortment of flowers from across the world accompanied by a few trees. With the abundance of Pokemon coming into the city, a few wild were bound to find and make this place there home. To ensure their safety, the City took inspiration from another project in Kalos. Thus, the first Wild Area was formed.

lights_district_wild_zone_2.name: Lights District - Wild Zone 2
lights_district_wild_zone_2.description: A large fountain that became a frequent spot for Wild Pokemon. It was quickly turned into a Wild Area after the first to prevent heavy foot-traffic and reduce littering into the water.

residential_district_beach.name: Residential District - Beach
residential_district_beach.description: A long, stretching beach across the edge of the Residential district. During the day it serves a purpose to sun-tanners and surfers for families all day, while the night provides a cool, romantic atmosphere guided by the relaxing sound of waves crashing- and thankfully only the very distant hum of the Lights district.

residential_district_dreamyard.name: Residential District - Dreamyard
residential_district_dreamyard.description: A run down area that used to be a place lots of scientists and researchers visited. It's hardly ever visited now, though. Pokemon drawn to a certain kind of energy seem to have taken up residence here, along with a strange individual locals have noticed.

residential_district_wild_zone_3.name: Residential District - Wild Zone 3
residential_district_wild_zone_3.description: A large section next to the beach formed entirely out of tidepools. Lots of Pokemon make the gaps and crevasses their home, which also makes it the perfect hunting ground for some birds hunting for an easy catch on some aquatic Pokemon.

residential_district_wild_zone_4.name: Residential District - Wild Zone 4
residential_district_wild_zone_4.description: A large abandoned building. It's actually a very nice place, that should've been really easy for a wealthy family to live in. Unfortunately, it became infested with ghost types that wanted to make it their home instead. Rather than trying to convince them to leave, the past owners just opted to let them have it. Since then, it's been turned into an official wild area for its protection.
